9. Product principles
Text is the command surface.
Routine manager and employee actions should happen via SMS whenever possible.
The website is the exception surface.
Use web only when precision, visualization, or bulk editing is genuinely needed.
Draft, then approve.
The system generates structure and recommendations; the manager keeps publishing control.
Coverage is the center of gravity.
Scheduling exists to make coverage faster, more accurate, and more automated.
Durable beats clever.
Backfill Shifts must remain usable even if no scheduler is ever connected.
Reuse beats re-entry.
Managers should rarely have to recreate a schedule from scratch.
Activation first, depth second.
The MVP must get customers live fast before expanding into richer planning features.
