19. Risks and mitigations
Risk: product becomes “yet another scheduler”

Mitigation: keep scope centered on schedule creation, publishing, callouts, and coverage.

Risk: roster data decays quickly

Mitigation: make CRUD and deactivation part of v1.

Risk: managers still prefer spreadsheets

Mitigation: make import fast, copy-last-week easy, and SMS approvals faster than spreadsheet editing.

Risk: employee messaging consent blocks adoption

Mitigation: manager-led enrollment assets, simple self-enrollment, clean confirmation flow, and visibility into who has/has not enrolled. Twilio and CTIA guidance make that opt-in and confirmation layer important for recurring messaging programs.

Risk: AI draft quality is not trusted

Mitigation: narrative exception summaries, transparent reasoning, manager override, and quick web review for conflicts.

